00:00:05:140000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:05:140000.Speaker: Howard

00:00:06:190000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:06:190000.Speaker: Voice
00:00:06:190000.Dialogue: Hey, Howard. Dave Roeger here at NASA. We need to talk about your upcoming mission.

00:00:11:070000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:11:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:11:070000.Dialogue: Yes, yes, I've been doing my push-ups.

00:00:15:070000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:15:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:15:070000.Dialogue: I'm still stuck at nine, but...

00:00:20:140000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:20:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:20:140000.Dialogue: ...that's going all the way down with no one holding me.

00:00:24:100000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:24:100000.Speaker: Roeger
00:00:24:100000.Dialogue: That's great, uh, but that's not why I called. We've run into a bit of a snafu. Your Soyuz capsule failed the pressurization test, so bottom line, mission's been scrubbed.

00:00:36:220000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:00:36:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:36:220000.Dialogue: You're kidding. So what does that mean? Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Boy, I got to tell you, I'm really disappointed. This was my dream ever since I was a little kid. Okay, well, uh, thanks for the call. Yep, you, too. Yes! Thank you! Oh! Oh...

00:01:04:170000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:01:04:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:04:170000.Dialogue: I'm not gonna die in space!

00:01:08:190000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. The phone rings. Howard puts it on speaker.
00:01:08:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:08:190000.Dialogue: I'm gonna die the way God intended, in my late 50s, with a heart full of pastrami.

00:01:45:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:45:020000.Dialogue: I'm going to need a larger shirt.

00:01:51:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:51:070000.Dialogue: This one's a little tight under the arms.

00:01:55:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:55:050000.Dialogue: Do you think maybe it's tight because you're wearing long underwear?

00:01:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:58:000000.Dialogue: Yes, of course that's why it's tight.

00:02:02:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:02:000000.Dialogue: All right, let me rephrase the question. Why are you wearing long underwear?

00:02:05:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:05:050000.Dialogue: You're kidding. Shouldn't the question be: why aren't you?

00:02:09:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:09:170000.Dialogue: No, it should be: why are you?

00:02:24:100000.Speaker: Assistant
00:02:24:100000.Dialogue: Why don't you slip this on?

00:02:26:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:26:070000.Dialogue: Said the hangman offering a noose.

00:02:29:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:29:140000.Dialogue: Well, that wasn't as entertaining as when he rents bowling shoes, but it was right up there.

00:02:35:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:35:000000.Dialogue: Well, that's it. My orders have been rescinded. I am officially no go to space.

00:02:41:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:41:070000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, Howard, but I got to tell you, I'm a little relieved you're not going.

00:02:46:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:46:140000.Dialogue: Come on, you were gonna go up in a rocket designed in the 1960s by the Russians.

00:02:52:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:52:020000.Dialogue: When was the last time you were at Best Buy and you heard someone say, Ooh, check out this Blu-ray player, it must be good, it was built in Russia?

00:03:00:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:00:120000.Dialogue: Well, their technology isn't that bad.

00:03:02:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:02:220000.Dialogue: When you come back to Earth in a Soyuz capsule, you free-fall from space at 500 miles per hour, and the only thing that slows you down is a little parachute that pops out right before you crash into the ground. And the whole thing was designed by the same brilliant minds who were unable to capture Rocky and Bullwinkle.

00:03:21:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:21:050000.Dialogue: All right, well, whatever. I wasn't worried.

00:03:25:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:25:050000.Dialogue: Let me explain the difference between you and me. You watch Star Trek; I live it.

00:03:34:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:34:170000.Dialogue: Oh, please. I don't remember the episode of Star Trek where the guy never goes to space and brags about it in a tuxedo store.

00:03:41:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:41:070000.Dialogue: Make all the jokes you want, but there's only one of us here brave enough to almost do what I almost did.

00:03:54:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:54:140000.Dialogue: A little. But not more than your urethras will be after whatever's in those pants swims up them.

00:04:02:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:02:140000.Dialogue: Well... I cut quite the dashing, yet hygienic figure, don't I? I look like the Flash about to get married.

00:04:13:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:13:220000.Dialogue: Oh! A tissue! A tissue! Oh, good Lord!

00:04:19:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:19:100000.Dialogue: He keeps emergency Purell in the car.

00:04:32:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:32:070000.Dialogue: For the record, not your worst opening line.

00:04:35:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:35:170000.Dialogue: Check it out. It's the gas I use in my free-electron laser to support high voltages. But it also has an interesting secondary use. Here. Breathe this in.

00:04:46:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:46:070000.Dialogue: B-Before I do it, if you're a cop you have tell me, right?

00:04:52:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:52:050000.Dialogue: Okay. What's it supposed to... Oh, my God, that's so freaky!

00:05:07:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:07:070000.Dialogue: Okay. Me, me, me. Ready? Leonard, I am your father.

00:05:15:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:15:120000.Dialogue: I have never been more attracted to a woman who sounds like a man in my life.

00:05:24:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:24:190000.Dialogue: Hey... you know how we've been... taking things slow?

00:05:30:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:30:070000.Dialogue: Well, I've been thinking, and... maybe I'm ready to... take things a little... faster.

00:05:39:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:39:020000.Dialogue: And I promise, after waiting four months, fast is what you're gonna get.

00:05:45:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:45:100000.Dialogue: You know, just-just one thing. Look, we're in a really great place right now, and I don't want to do anything that will make stuff all weird again.

00:05:51:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:51:220000.Dialogue: So we won't let it get weird.

00:05:53:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:53:190000.Dialogue: Okay. Oh, and just a heads-up... mm, since the last time you saw me naked, I got a Cookie Monster tattoo. The acceptable responses when you see it are awesome or nothing.

00:06:21:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:21:070000.Dialogue: It's not an accident. I waited outside your door for 20 minutes.

00:06:28:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:28:120000.Dialogue: I must say, I was surprised you chose to spend our date night in your apartment. As I mentioned, the Pasadena City Council is debating longer crosswalk times, and later, the LEGO store is having a midnight madness sale. You ask anyone, that's a hot date.

00:06:44:170000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:44:170000.Dialogue: Tempting choices, but I have something special planned for tonight.

00:06:49:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:49:000000.Dialogue: What can be more special than having an adequate amount of time to cross the street on your way to buy a tiny LEGO Indiana Jones?

00:06:56:120000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:56:120000.Dialogue: With our friends moving forward in their relationships, I've decided that we should make progress in ours as well.

00:07:04:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:04:050000.Dialogue: Two years ago, we didn't even know each other, and now I'm in your apartment after dark.

00:07:11:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:11:000000.Dialogue: How much faster can this thing go?

00:07:14:000000.Speaker: Amy
00:07:14:000000.Dialogue: I had a feeling you'd be reluctant, which is why I'm going to dip into my neurobiological bag of tricks.

00:07:19:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:19:120000.Dialogue: Oh, you brain monkeys kill me. Dip away.

00:07:23:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:07:23:220000.Dialogue: I have devised an experiment that I believe will increase your feelings for me in an accelerated time frame.

00:07:29:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:29:140000.Dialogue: And how do you propose to do that? Uh, hope you're not thinking about some sort of LSD thought control.

00:07:35:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:35:170000.Dialogue: Because there's only one mind-expanding drug that this man enjoys, and that's called school.

00:07:41:050000.Speaker: Amy
00:07:41:050000.Dialogue: Human beings form emotional attachments as they grow up. In your case, to your mother, superheroes, et cetera. I'm going to attempt an experiment that will get you to transfer those feelings to me.

00:07:53:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:53:000000.Dialogue: Well, seems what's on the menu tonight is malarkey with a big side of poppycock.

00:07:59:000000.Speaker: Amy
00:07:59:000000.Dialogue: We'll see. Let's start with a little romantic dinner music, shall we?

00:08:10:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:10:170000.Dialogue: I see what you're doing. You're attempting to build on the work of Ebbinghaus by triggering an involuntary memory of me playing that game-- admittedly the happiest 600 hours of my childhood...

00:08:24:190000.Speaker: Amy
00:08:24:190000.Dialogue: Fine. There's no reason we still can't have a lovely dinner. Why don't you have a seat.

00:08:35:000000.Speaker: Amy
00:08:35:000000.Dialogue: May I offer you something to drink?

00:08:45:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:45:100000.Dialogue: It's my favorite pink fluid, narrowly beating out Pepto-Bismol.

00:08:51:140000.Speaker: Amy
00:08:51:140000.Dialogue: Oh, I know. I think it will go nicely with what I have prepared... for dinner.

00:08:58:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:58:220000.Dialogue: Spaghetti with little pieces of hot dog cut up in it!

00:09:02:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:09:02:220000.Dialogue: Just like your mommy used to make.

00:09:04:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:04:020000.Dialogue: Oh... yummy, yummy! We should do this more often.

00:09:21:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:21:170000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. I did, I crossed a line. I didn't mean to!

00:09:24:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:24:100000.Dialogue: Who says something like that right in the middle of sex?!

00:09:26:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:26:070000.Dialogue: I don't know, it just came out. People say weird things during sex all the time.

00:09:31:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:31:020000.Dialogue: Okay, well, they sure as hell don't say that.

00:09:33:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:33:100000.Dialogue: It was the heat of the moment.

00:09:41:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:41:100000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. Just-just give me another chance.

00:09:44:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:44:120000.Dialogue: Why, so you can crawl under the covers and go, Hey, baby, want to go look for houses in neighborhoods with good schools?

00:09:50:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:50:120000.Dialogue: Again, I'm sorry. You know, with Howard and Bernadette getting married, I got caught up in a little wedding fever. I take it back.

00:09:57:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:57:100000.Dialogue: You can't take something like that back. I mean, what are we even supposed to do now?

00:10:02:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:02:190000.Dialogue: Okay, at some point, we'll look back and this is going to be a funny story. Why don't we just start doing that now?

00:10:17:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:17:050000.Dialogue: ...that time when I proposed to you in bed?

00:10:22:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:22:170000.Dialogue: And you were all, like, What are you doing?

00:10:27:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:27:050000.Dialogue: That was so funny. So funny.

00:10:38:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:38:120000.Dialogue: Is that a little smile I see there? I should go.

00:10:46:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:46:020000.Dialogue: Hey, I was thinking. For our first dance at the wedding, what if we learn the final number from Dirty Dancing?

00:11:02:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:02:190000.Dialogue: you lifting me up into the air.

00:11:06:120000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:06:120000.Dialogue: Oh, you're in a good mood.

00:11:08:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:08:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, why wouldn't I be? You know, I'm marrying the girl of my dreams, and I finally got my mother to agree not to come on our honeymoon.

00:11:17:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:17:170000.Dialogue: Oh, hang on. Oh, it's NASA. Wolowitz. Oh! Hi, Dave. What's up? No kidding. Really?

00:11:36:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:36:070000.Dialogue: Great, great news. All right, I'll watch my e-mail for the details. Okay, talk soon.

00:11:48:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:48:170000.Dialogue: It looks like I'm going into space after all.

00:12:08:050000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:08:050000.Dialogue: What happened? I thought they canceled your mission.

00:12:09:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:09:190000.Dialogue: Th-They did. But NASA really wants my telescope up on the space station, so they're putting me on an earlier launch.

00:12:23:170000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:23:170000.Dialogue: What? We're getting married that Sunday.

00:12:27:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:27:170000.Dialogue: You're right! I-I can't go to space. I have to get married, and no one can say that's not a good reason. I'll call him back.

00:12:37:070000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:37:070000.Dialogue: Wait. I don't want to be the one who stands in your way.

00:12:40:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:40:190000.Dialogue: Well, too bad, you already did. It's a done deal. Oh, well. But I forgive you.

00:12:44:190000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:44:190000.Dialogue: No. That's not how I want to start our marriage, killing your dream? We'll have the wedding when you get back.

00:12:50:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:50:100000.Dialogue: But wh-what about all the plans and the guests?

00:12:54:220000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:12:54:220000.Dialogue: We'll call them. Although my dad's gonna go a little nutso over losing his deposits.

00:13:04:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:04:000000.Dialogue: Your dad's gonna be furious. There's no way he's gonna let us postpone this wedding. Well, we tried.

00:13:11:100000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:13:11:100000.Dialogue: I'll talk to him. He won't say no to his little girl.

00:13:12:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:12:170000.Dialogue: No! I-I should talk to him, man to man.

00:13:19:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:13:19:140000.Dialogue: But, Howie, my dad can be a bully. He's gonna make you cancel your space flight.

00:13:23:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:23:100000.Dialogue: We can only hope... that he doesn't.

00:13:28:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:13:28:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:28:020000.Dialogue: Bishop to queen four, level two. Check.

00:13:35:220000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:13:35:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:35:220000.Dialogue: Sheldon... knight takes bishop. You all right?

00:13:41:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:13:41:020000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:44:070000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:13:44:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:44:070000.Dialogue: Are you? You left your queen exposed from above, you trapped your knight in the corner, and you keep sighing and saying, Why me?

00:13:54:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:13:54:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:54:120000.Dialogue: Very well. Can I ask you a question about women?

00:14:00:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:00:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:00:020000.Dialogue: We got you that book last year. Wasn't everything in there?

00:14:04:070000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:04:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:04:070000.Dialogue: No, I'm having a relationship problem with Amy. And by the way, that book gave me nightmares.

00:14:11:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:11:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:11:140000.Dialogue: Well, if it makes you feel any better, I screwed things up pretty good with Penny.

00:14:17:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:17:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:17:020000.Dialogue: Look at us, Leonard... engaging in the social convention of men bellyaching about their ol' ladies.

00:14:24:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:24:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:24:140000.Dialogue: I guess we are. So, what's going on?

00:14:29:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:29:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:29:120000.Dialogue: Believe it or not, Amy has embarked on a campaign to increase my feelings for her by making me happy.

00:14:39:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:39:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:39:120000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, that must be very difficult for you.

00:14:43:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:43:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:43:140000.Dialogue: It's awful. This morning, she arranged for me to be an Amtrak junior conductor for the day. It-It's usually only open to children. She got them to make an exception.

00:14:55:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:55:140000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:58:000000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:14:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:58:000000.Dialogue: They let me blow the whistle, Leonard.

00:15:00:220000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:00:220000.Speaker: Leonard

00:15:04:000000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:04:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:04:000000.Dialogue: I know. And it gets worse. Her efforts are causing me to have affectionate feelings for her at inappropriate times.

00:15:15:050000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:15:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:15:050000.Dialogue: You mean, like in bed or in the shower?

00:15:18:190000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:18:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:18:190000.Dialogue: No! Would you please stop referencing that infernal book?

00:15:24:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:24:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:24:140000.Dialogue: For example, this morning, I was calculating the random motion of virtual particles in a vacuum, when suddenly the particles morphed into an image of Amy's dandruff...

00:15:40:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:40:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:40:100000.Dialogue: ...gently cascading down onto her pale, slightly hunched shoulders.

00:15:47:050000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:47:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:47:050000.Dialogue: What has that vixen done to me, Leonard?

00:15:50:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:50:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:50:100000.Dialogue: And how do I make it stop?

00:15:52:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:52:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:52:020000.Dialogue: Well, if you had a physical relationship, I'd say propose during sex. Turns out that's a real mood killer.

00:15:59:170000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:15:59:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:59:170000.Dialogue: I assume we're talking about you now?

00:16:01:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:16:01:120000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:02:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:16:02:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:02:100000.Dialogue: So, that's how this works? I complain, and then you complain, and no one offers any solutions?

00:16:08:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:16:08:140000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:11:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon and Leonard are playing three dimensional chess.
00:16:11:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:11:100000.Dialogue: Well, no wonder the women are winning.

00:16:20:140000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:16:20:140000.Dialogue: Oh, just looking at some old pictures. Come on in.

00:16:23:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:23:070000.Dialogue: Family pictures, or...? H-Holy crap, that's a dead person.

00:16:28:020000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:16:28:020000.Dialogue: Last murder case before I retired. How many bodies do you see there? Careful, it's a trick question.

00:16:39:000000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:16:39:000000.Dialogue: Nah, you'll never get it. It's a fraction.

00:16:43:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:43:050000.Dialogue: How about that. Anyway, sir, I need to talk to you about something.

00:16:54:220000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:16:54:220000.Dialogue: Oh, sure. My partner used to have that. He's dead now.

00:17:06:020000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:17:06:020000.Dialogue: But she was nuts, so in a way...

00:17:11:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:11:000000.Dialogue: Nice story. Anyway, the reason I wanted to talk to you is NASA has moved up my launch to the International Space Station.

00:17:42:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:42:020000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. May I be excused?

00:17:46:100000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:17:46:100000.Dialogue: No, you may not. Let me tell you something. When I first met you... You just gonna stand there?

00:17:52:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:52:140000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, I didn't know, is this going to... Well, I should sit... May I be seat... Well, I'll just sit.

00:18:01:070000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:18:01:070000.Dialogue: When I first met you, I didn't like you.

00:18:08:190000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:18:08:190000.Dialogue: But then you and I had some time together.

00:18:18:000000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:18:18:000000.Dialogue: That silly Beatle haircut and... you riding around on a red Vespa, and you're still living at home with your mother. To be honest, I thought Bernadette chose you to punish me.

00:18:32:140000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:18:32:140000.Dialogue: But then I heard about your astronaut thing, and I realized I judged you too fast. Maybe you are the right guy for my little girl.

00:18:42:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:42:140000.Dialogue: Oh, I am. And just so you know, I'd still be an astronaut, even if I didn't go to space. I've got an I.D. card and a NASA golf shirt.

00:18:52:020000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:18:52:020000.Dialogue: No, no, you got to go. You can't turn down an opportunity like this.

00:18:55:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:55:190000.Dialogue: B-But what about the wedding and all the money you put down for the reception?

00:19:00:220000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:19:00:220000.Dialogue: You let me worry about that. You go up to that space station, and you make me proud.

00:19:13:140000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:19:13:140000.Dialogue: You got a problem with that?

00:19:15:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:15:140000.Dialogue: All right, look, I'm gonna level with you. I'm terrified about going into space. What if I don't make it back?

00:19:31:000000.Speaker: Mr. Rostenkowski
00:19:31:000000.Dialogue: Of course. A pretty girl like Bernadette... she'll find a new guy.

00:19:58:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:58:140000.Dialogue: Penny, just, wait. I've been thinking about what I said when we were in bed the other night.

00:20:04:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:04:000000.Dialogue: Yeah, I've been thinking about it, too.

00:20:06:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:06:020000.Dialogue: I noticed you never answered me.

00:20:20:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:20:140000.Dialogue: Uh, follow-up. Are we still dating?

00:20:24:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:24:020000.Dialogue: Is it still weird 'cause I proposed?

00:20:27:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:27:120000.Dialogue: I have a couple more quick questions. Do you want to call me from the car?

00:20:34:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:34:020000.Dialogue: Think I played that pretty well.
